	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p><hi rend="underline"><add>Yiddish</add></hi></p>
				<p>May God seek the peace of the man<lb/> of his covenant I extend to him my<lb/> covenant of peace.  My friend&#44; who is like a<lb/> brother to me. The &#8220;Zaddick&#8221; of clean hands<lb/> and a pure heart&#44; the all&#45;embracing wise<lb/> man&#44; our teacher <persName>Rabbi Isaac Leeser</persName>.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Honored Friend&#58;</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">I have prevailed upon the trustees<lb/> that it is time to send you money.  No one<lb/> had anything against it&#44; but before they<lb/> would pay&#44; the people wanted to be urged on the<lb/> matter&#44; and I did not like to urge them for<lb/> they might suppose I made a profit from this<lb/> business&#44; since the book cost them so very much.<lb/> I should therefore very much appreciate<lb/> your sending immediately a letter<lb/> to the treasurers&#44; <persName>Moses Bronner</persName>&#44; of the firm of<lb/> <persName>Bronner and Seburg<add>&#63;</add></persName>&#44; and at the same time<lb/> to me in which you earnestly demand<lb/> money. In view of the fact that I had pro&#45;<lb/>mised to send you the money the first<lb/> of this month. I am convinced that you will<lb/> then receive the money by return mail.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I want to inform you that the<lb/> organization called Harmonia&#44; consisting<lb/> of 18 of the most intelligent Jews of this<lb/> town&#44; which was organized only two<lb/> months ago&#44; sent a very handsome <date>Purim</date><lb/> gift to <persName role="author">Dr. Illoway</persName>&#44; namely a very pretty</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>silver cup. The outside bears a very<lb/> fitting inscription and the inside was<lb/> filled with a considerable sum of money.<lb/> Since I am concerned with the honor and<lb/> not with the sum. I keep quiet about it&#44;<lb/> but <sic>it</sic> any case I want you to know<lb/> that it was no less than &#36;150 and thus a<lb/> fitting enough sum to show their appreciation of<lb/> the doctor whom they made an honorary member.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I surely expect to see my Hebrew<lb/> letter in the &#8220;Occident&#8221; this month&#44; and I<lb/> already  have an answer to <persName>Einhorn</persName> in<lb/> order to show him how unjustly he treats you&#44;<lb/> how false the charge is that original sin is a<lb/> Christian idea. That may very well be but it was<lb/> taken from the Jews. That sin is inherited&#44; you may<lb/> find in the Talmud&#44; especially fre&#45;<lb/>quently in the &#8220;Ba&#39;al Akaida.&#8221;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Yours devotedly&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)"><persName role="author">Dr. Illoway</persName></p>
				<p rend="Line drawn from &#8220;Ba&#45;al Akeda&#8221; to the following.">a <sic>mediaeval</sic> philosophical commentary</p>
